\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li624\ri0\lin624\rin0\fi-624\f4\fs22\f3\f3\fs20\sl360\slmult1\qj \'0353]\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\cf0\sl360\slmult1\qj\ls0\li624\ri0\lin624\rin0\fi-624\rtlch\af3\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f4\fs22\lang7177\loch\f4\fs22\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0 Now as a body charged with defending and promoting competitive market structures, we undoubtedly welcome competition between what had been two geographically separated distribution businesses, just as we welcome the prospect of enhanced competition between
 the {\ltrch\hich\i\loch\i Mercury }and the {\ltrch\hich\i\loch\i Witness.}  Indeed in our view one of several manifestly positive outcomes of MM\'92s decision to sever ties with IN in favour of a contract with NW is that it has ultimately compelled NW to establish a distribution network in Durban.  But 
